'''Waves4Power''' is a developer of buoy-based Offshore Wave Energy Converter (OWEC) systems. There are plans to install a demonstration plant in 2015 at the [[Runde Environmental Centre]] in [[Norway]]. There they will be testing the '''WaveEL''', an offshore buoy. This will be connected via sub-sea cable to the shore based power grid.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Ollson|first1=Maria|title=Country Report: Sweden|url=http://report2014.ocean-energy-systems.org/country-reports/sweden/technology-demonstration/|website=Ocean Energy Systems|accessdate=29 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Tomasgard|first1=Anne-Mari|title=BELIEVES IN GJENNOMBROT FOR WAVE ENERGY|url=http://www.heroynytt.no/nyheter/2015/09/01/Trur-p%C3%A5-gjennombrot-for-b%C3%B8lgekraft-11493227.ece|website=Herønytt|accessdate=29 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Tomasgard|first1=Anne-Mari|title=Believe in Breakthrough for Wave Energy|url=http://www.smp.no/nyheter/2015/09/01/Trur-p%C3%A5-gjennombrot-for-b%C3%B8lgekraft-11493227.ece|accessdate=29 October 2015|agency=Sunnmørsposten|publisher=Hanna Relling Berg|date=12 October 2015}}</ref>
